pan(25.10)                                                          pan(25.10)

Name
       pan  - Specifies that the new center of the viewing window should shift
       from the current center of the viewing window by (<x>, <y>) microns

Syntax
       pan

       [-help]

       <dx>

       <d><y>

       Specifies that the new center of the viewing window should  shift  from
       the  current  center  of  the viewing window by (<x>, <y>) microns. Use
       this command at any stage in the design flow to pan or move the  design
       view in a specific direction.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each pan parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man pan.

       <dx>   Specifies  that the design center should shift dx microns on the
              x-axis from the center of the viewing window.

              You can specify positive or negative values for dx.  A  positive
              value specifies shifting to the right on the x axis.

       <dy>   Specifies  that the design center should shift dy microns on the
              y axis values from the center of the viewing window.

              You can specify positive or negative values for <dy>. A positive
              value specifies shifting up on the y axis.

Example
       The following example shifts the design center to the right by 200  mi-
       crons and down by 300 microns from the center of the viewing window.

       pan 200 -300

